    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "cbe9036a9a922af6",
      "text": "Methods overview. a The human and chimpanzee cortex were constructed using MRI data, with chimpanzee-to-human cortical expansion computed based on the reconstructed cortical maps. b Genes associated with human accelerated regions (HAR), which represent genomic loci with accelerated divergence in humans, were examined. c Cortical gene expression of HAR genes and HAR-BRAIN genes were examined using human transcription data from the Allen Human Brain Atlas (AHBA) and comparative transcription data of the human, chimpanzee, and macaque from the PsychENCODE database."
